<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-12-0965 </DOCNO><TEXT>An insight into the political mechanics of American international oilpolicy in the past long decade from 1973 to early 1986 of highly pricedcrude oil is presented. It is the intention to delineate the link fromUnited States policy to the political organization of the internationaloil system. Domestic and foreign oil policies, economic relations aspolitical leverage, oil and security policy, domestic restraints andforeign policy demands are reviewed and the American oil system strategyis discussed.</TEXT></DOC>